<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="754" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.773/38.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Guthrie</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 234, March 8. Consul, Dairen, telegraphs discrimination against
                            American vessels still exists. Request Foreign Office to instruct
                            railway authorities to grant the reduced rates to shipments in other
                            than Japanese vessels whether to Newchwang or Dairen as necessary to
                            preserve open door.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>